32	avalon_20251201_005546	Bob	good	good	proposal	100300	100300	\N	I know I’m good, and Mission 2 guarantees at least one evil among Alice/Charlie, so the two evils are drawn from {Alice, Charlie, Eve, Diana} with at least one of {Alice, Charlie} evil. Under that constraint, the chance that Eve is evil is the same as for Diana, but including myself (known-good to me) makes a 2-person team with a 60% success chance vs 40% fail, better than any pair that doesn’t include me. Between Eve and Diana, Eve’s been lightly stress-tested by being leader on a successful Mission 1 and is broadly trusted at the table, and her preference for pairing with someone from the M2 block (rather than two totally untested players) is consistent with a good mindset. So Bob + Eve maximizes the success odds while keeping at least one player with prior mission history on the team.	\N	[0.008937329,0.009503243,-0.021100584,-0.051012486,-0.014277884,-0.0066238516,0.00035587166,0.038167596,0.013600812,0.041298714,-0.052383628,-0.005857342,0.08238657,-0.06336377,0.004458248,0.07686291,0.06281388,0.02016101,-0.015278422,0.037868444,-0.11584493,-0.12908833,0.012989447,-0.029913537,-0.019946013,0.016657878,-0.025410788,0.028798843,-0.014887109,-0.114006884,0.003488844,0.025299983,0.052851867,0.025280792,-0.049209725,-0.0068127187,-0.030778462,-0.014386293,-0.022271743,-0.03134513,0.005451527,-0.0016666417,0.0056076823,-0.077192046,-0.09845421,-0.016961236,0.023629801,0.05336096,0.005987781,-0.053856365,-0.023624681,-0.005051345,-0.013361306,-0.007485802,0.038956903,0.060482368,-0.04812613,0.029524721,-0.05108167,0.031214155,0.0013775011,0.05100879,-0.046876017,0.01217148,0.0954876,0.004131445,-0.028566089,0.064182535,-0.07633249,0.033064827,0.053371012,-0.06472795,-0.09197073,-0.06442846,0.0023891726,0.03285524,0.054421972,-0.011942665,0.060463954,0.028205223,-0.023629999,-0.039678667,0.02061936,0.09260627,0.022695,-0.041997846,-0.016313232,-0.047304098,0.094367325,0.040875457,-0.033399235,-0.018237146