157	avalon_20251201_003138	Diana	good	good	proposal	100500	100500	\N	Given the mission history and everyone’s stated preferences, the most consistent world is that Alice and Bob are the two evil players, which makes Charlie and Eve both good.\\n\\nKey points:\\n- Mission 3 (Alice + Charlie) failed, and Mission 4 (Charlie + Diana + Bob) failed. With me (Diana) known good to myself, Mission 4’s fail forces at least one evil in {Charlie, Bob}. Mission 3 forces at least one evil in {Alice, Charlie}.\\n- The only globally consistent evil pairs are: {Alice, Bob}, {Charlie, Alice}, {Charlie, Bob}, or {Charlie, Eve}.\\n- Bob’s suggestion of the team [Diana, Eve, Alice] would be an all-good team if {Charlie, Bob} were evil, which is strongly against his interest as evil; this makes {Charlie, Bob} the least likely evil pair.\\n- Both Charlie and Eve independently converge on including {Diana, Eve} as auto-locks and argue to add Charlie; that pattern is exactly what we’d expect if they are good and see Alice/Bob as more suspicious.\\n- In the {Alice, Bob} evil world, the team [Charlie, Diana, Eve] is all good and wins the game. In the alternative worlds where Charlie is evil, at least one of Eve/Alice/Bob is also evil and the table talk from Bob becomes less coherent from an evil perspective.\\n\\nPutting this together, the highest-probability good team is [Charlie, Diana, Eve], so that’s the team I propose.	\N	[-0.026055766,0.040736493,-0.03164377,-0.071225874,-0.034281015,0.045957197,0.0046904627,-0.04037527,-0.015295952,0.087921344,-0.0017124233,-0.0016862912,0.086194895,-0.062194023,0.006502359,0.059109226,-0.014592319,-0.0069366773,-0.08245697,0.039163142,-0.027210366,-0.13836035,-0.009681502,-0.001014883,-0.050892856,0.038960338,0.007899044,0.01113496,-0.030119365,-0.10575128,-0.040789627,0.08129685,0.07433534,0.026705166,-0.00577266,0.051538657,-0.018433874,0.008162868,0.014417232,0.010009095,-0.049142353,-0.03168352,-0.027935898,-0.040738817,-0.08073682,0.026525887,-0.