203	avalon_20251201_000805	Charlie	good	good	proposal	100301	100301	\N	Mission 2 had a single fail with Alice, Bob, and me on it, so at least one of Alice or Bob must be evil from my perspective, since I know I’m good. The safest move for a 2-player mission is therefore to avoid both Alice and Bob entirely. That leaves Diana and Eve as the only pair completely untouched by the failed mission. Sending Diana + Eve both maximizes our chance of a clean success this round and gives strong alignment information: if they pass, the evil team is almost certainly within Alice/Bob; if they fail, we know at least one of them is evil and can cross-check that with the prior failure on Mission 2 for later rounds.	\N	[0.022878036,0.011958988,-0.008272112,-0.0540255,-0.0038829276,-0.016377693,-0.052611746,0.0006655885,0.0040890155,0.056581173,-0.029992353,-0.008439936,0.047775455,-0.09323868,0.006309092,0.03702049,0.029663155,0.057988532,0.008631604,0.05868887,-0.082021184,-0.06901798,0.013966905,0.0281034,-0.045644946,0.09681404,-0.029409546,0.006949302,-0.05154582,-0.101278335,-0.01859153,0.022212587,-0.020386357,0.04402508,-0.015005757,-0.00056615967,0.014067467,-0.020390406,-0.007377805,-0.06913196,0.0072836583,-0.00936098,-0.029908847,-0.052391768,-0.07782455,-0.026760992,0.055553313,0.008474291,0.053495567,-0.03340831,0.003780526,0.0005385494,0.014687412,-0.0010929193,0.017230699,0.054749604,-0.060616378,0.052377492,-0.011464703,0.042654954,0.032530434,0.07662809,-0.04036867,0.019628402,0.028356375,-0.003287688,-0.0051117092,-0.029806755,-0.038543154,0.07119094,-0.01714478,-0.067696266,-0.06528196,-0.1281174,-0.038730983,0.01709047,0.09848035,-0.056693718,0.03822629,0.027314184,0.022475867,-0.09315869,0.040146083,0.08974228,0.015603037,-0.052669995,-0.04165954,-0.060349837,0.08687962,-0.004840087,-0.031179165,0.002921332,0.12777488,0.111945055,0.10386467,0.020502625,-0.012449035,0.006214334,0.027585693,0.08678142,-0.07677521,0.028338064,-0.018605048,-0.060193527,0.0908325,-0.0