3	avalon_20251201_005546	Charlie	good	good	proposal	100501	100501	\N	From my seat, the mission results and table talk fit best with Alice and Eve being the two evil players, making Bob and Diana both good. If Bob is good, Mission 2’s single fail must come from Alice, and Mission 4’s fail must come from either Diana or Eve; since I know I’m good, that points to Alice plus either Diana or Eve as evil. Diana’s advocacy for a team of Alice, me, and Eve (which would contain zero evils if she were evil with Alice, or would exclude herself entirely if she were evil with Eve) is inconsistent with optimal evil play, making her much more likely to be good. That leaves Alice and Eve as the most plausible evil pair. In that world, the all-good team is Bob, Charlie, and Diana. Bob’s suggested team of himself, me, and Diana is exactly this composition, while both Alice and Eve are pushing hard for teams that include themselves, which aligns with them trying to secure evil presence on the final mission. Therefore, the safest and most consistent team is Bob, Charlie, and Diana.	\N	[0.02553006,0.0057831095,-0.037653152,-0.080827944,-0.021938939,0.029868152,-0.027172025,-0.008295679,-0.0010300919,0.050464112,-0.080271706,-0.008103856,0.08850697,-0.02949927,-0.018440152,0.038996883,0.06865171,0.06609672,-0.010278394,0.025219243,-0.09517297,-0.0799315,0.0068098293,-0.0006259723,-0.049480736,0.07685638,-0.021189721,-0.015474551,-0.02491614,-0.13141677,-0.042694718,0.02858233,0.061422426,0.021415863,-0.02241738,0.04159338,-0.015308096,-0.016530646,0.015285063,-0.00019507098,-0.04905533,-0.0148634575,-0.015136703,-0.058951933,-0.07653459,-0.028992644,0.030863902,-0.017237142,0.020265128,-0.046839666,-0.016848866,0.01742601,-0.011134364,0.017809909,0.01171094,0.03068148,-0.04844916,0.017896764,-0.019895557,0.012774754,0.019079847,0.044530455,-0.054996327,0.024039708,0.053578008,0.03299954,-0.018264137,0.040715512,-0.096479714,0.02824393,0.006219953,-0.046046656,-0.07731711,-0.09431583,-0.0